# 19. Which protocols use TCP and UDP?

| Protocol | Transport Protocol          |
| -------- | --------------------------- |
| HTTP     | TCP                         |
| HTTPS    | TCP                         |
| TLS      | TCP                         |
| DNS      | Usually UDP (sometimes TCP) |
| DHCP     | UDP                         |

---

# 20. OSI Layer Mapping

| OSI Layer   | Protocol/Technology        |
| ----------- | -------------------------- |
| Application | HTTP, HTTPS, DNS, TLS      |
| Transport   | TCP, UDP                   |
| Network     | IP                         |
| Data Link   | Ethernet, MAC, ARP         |
| Physical    | Bits, Cable, Wi-Fi Signals |

---

# 21. Complete Web Flow

```text
User types google.com
        │
Browser Cache
        │
DNS Resolution
        │
Google IP Found
        │
Subnet Check
        │
ARP (Router MAC Found)
        │
TCP 3-Way Handshake
        │
TLS Handshake
        │
HTTP Request
        │
HTTP Response
        │
Browser Renders HTML/CSS/JS
        │
Google Homepage Displayed
```

---

# 22. One-Line Interview Summary

> **When a user enters a website URL, the browser checks its cache, resolves the domain name using DNS, establishes a reliable TCP connection, secures it with TLS,
sends an HTTP request, receives the HTTP response, and finally renders the webpage for the user.**


